===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|thurghfare|lang=enm}}, corresponding to {{compound|through|fare}}. Compare Old English {{term|þurhfaran||to go through, go over, traverse, pierce, pass through, pass beyond, transcend, penetrate|lang=ang}}. Compare also {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|þurhfær||inner secret place|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Durchfahrt||passage through, thoroughfare|lang=de}}.

